charls
------------------------------------------
CharLS is a C++ implementation of the JPEG-LS standard for lossless and
near-lossless image compression and decompression. JPEG-LS is a low-complexity
image compression standard that matches JPEG 2000 compression ratios.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.4-1
  libcharls-devel-2.1.0-1bl1
  libcharls2-2.1.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/team-charls/charls

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/team-charls/charls/archive/2.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack charls-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./charls-2.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/charls-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/charls-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcharls2-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcharls-devel-2.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(charls)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/charls.README
  /usr/share/doc/charls/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/charls/LICENSE.md
  /usr/share/doc/charls/README.md

(libcharls2)
  /usr/bin/cygcharls-2.dll

(libcharls-devel)
  /usr/include/charls/api_abi.h
  /usr/include/charls/charls.h
  /usr/include/charls/charls_legacy.h
  /usr/include/charls/jpegls_error.h
  /usr/include/charls/public_types.h
  /usr/include/charls/version.h
  /usr/lib/libcharls.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/charls.pc

